[10] Israel
Date: Sat 28 May 2022
Source: The Times of Israel [edited]
https://www.timesofisrael.com/israel-reports-second-case-of-monkeypox-in-30-year-old-man/


Israel has confirmed a 2nd case of the rare monkeypox virus, in a 30-year-old man who recently returned from an overseas trip.

The man was hospitalized on Friday [27 May 2022] at the Sheba Medical Center in Tel Aviv, and was released after a short while. He was confirmed to be infected with the virus on Saturday [28 May 2022].

The new infection came just over a week after Israel discovered its 1st case of the virus, in a man in his 30s who had returned from a trip to western Europe.

Israeli health officials have played down the risk of the virus. In a phone briefing last Sunday [22 May 2022], the Health Ministry's head of public health services, Dr. Sharon Alroy-Preis, urged calm and said the recent outbreak of the virus was not a major risk to public health.

A case of the virus was diagnosed in Israel in 2018, and no known community infections resulted from it.

[Byline: Michael Horovitz]

